{
  "texts": [
    "The canonical bundle, which we denote by K Σ, is the +i-eigenspace.",
    "The vector bundle ad P (𝔭 C) = P × K C 𝔭 C is associated to P via the adjoint representation of K C on 𝔭 C. In a local complex coordinate z, the holomorphic sections of K Σ are given by f dz, where f is a holomorphic function.",
    "Thus, in local coordinates, a holomorphic section of K Σ ⊗ (ad P (𝔭 C)) is given by A dz, where A is a holomorphic map into 𝔭 C. Example 4.5 (SL n (C)-Higgs bundles, [AABC + 19, Def. 2.4]).",
    "We claim that an SL n (C)-Higgs bundle (P, Φ) can be described equivalently in terms of a Higgs vector bundle: a pair (E, Φ) where E is a holomorphic vector bundle with Λ n E ≃ O Σ and Φ:E → K Σ ⊗ E is a trace-free endomorphism twisted by K Σ.Indeed, given a holomorphic K C = SL n (C)-bundle P, we can consider the associated vector bundle E = P × SLn(C) C n corresponding to the defining representation.",
    "Notice that Λ n E ≃ O Σ is holomorphically trivial."
  ]
}